WEBVTT

00:08.624 --> 00:10.292
What a day!

00:10.359 --> 00:13.628
Binford's executive
schlockmeister, Morgan Wandell,

00:13.696 --> 00:17.265
wants me to do a whole
<i>Tool Time</i> just talking.

00:17.333 --> 00:20.868
No tools, no projects,
no hands-on anything!

00:20.936 --> 00:23.238
Isn't that insane?

00:23.306 --> 00:25.473
How many "P's" in "deposit"?

00:27.009 --> 00:28.076
Two!

00:30.012 --> 00:31.879
I was right.

00:31.947 --> 00:33.281
Now more about me...

00:33.349 --> 00:34.916
No. Sorry, man.
I can't. I'm in a hurry.

00:34.983 --> 00:37.885
I gotta go put a security deposit
down on my new apartment.

00:37.953 --> 00:39.220
Brad, listen to this...

00:39.288 --> 00:41.026
Actually, Dad, can you
talk to me about it later?

00:41.056 --> 00:42.361
I have a 5:00 hair
appointment at Pablo's.

00:42.391 --> 00:43.529
He gets all weird when I'm late.

00:43.559 --> 00:44.859
Pablo?

00:44.926 --> 00:46.694
He's more important
than your dad?

00:46.762 --> 00:48.563
Dad, he cuts my hair.

00:51.900 --> 00:53.634
Hey, Mark,
you gotta listen to this.

00:53.702 --> 00:56.971
Sure. As soon as I'm done
watching this show.

00:57.039 --> 01:01.042
You're watching <i>Cooking
with the Ragin' Cajun?</i>

01:01.110 --> 01:02.910
Dad, it's Gumbo Week.

01:04.813 --> 01:07.215
Hi. How was
your day, honey?

01:07.283 --> 01:08.549
Terrible. Terrible.

01:08.617 --> 01:10.555
- Why? What happened?
- Sit down and I'll tell you.

01:10.585 --> 01:13.154
Morgan Wandell now is taking
complete control of the show, right?

01:13.222 --> 01:14.693
- Yeah.
- I'm used to things being my way.

01:14.723 --> 01:16.683
I'm not gonna take orders
from a cheesy young punk

01:16.725 --> 01:18.063
- who thinks he knows production.
- Hey, Mom?

01:18.093 --> 01:19.331
- We're talking.
- It's Professor Hanover's office.

01:19.361 --> 01:20.632
- We're talking.
- Dr. Hanover? Wait.

01:20.662 --> 01:22.267
Just hold that thought.
I just have to take this call.

01:22.297 --> 01:23.964
Hello?

01:24.833 --> 01:25.933
Yeah.

01:26.001 --> 01:27.335
Yeah.

01:27.403 --> 01:31.605
Yeah, I can have a meeting with Dr.
Hanover, Thursday, 2:00.

01:36.778 --> 01:41.149
Can you tell me what
this meeting is about?

01:41.216 --> 01:45.520
Well, I guess I'll just have to
find out when I get there. Okay.

01:45.587 --> 01:47.488
All right. Thanks. Bye.

01:48.657 --> 01:50.058
Howdy.

01:50.125 --> 01:51.630
Dr. Hanover wants to have
a meeting with me.

01:51.660 --> 01:53.061
That's great.
Anyway, this guy...

01:53.128 --> 01:54.628
No, it's not great.
I mean,

01:54.696 --> 01:56.601
maybe he reread my thesis and
he's having second thoughts.

01:56.631 --> 01:58.066
Honey? Honey, please?

01:58.133 --> 01:59.405
Maybe he found a reference
that's outdated.

01:59.435 --> 02:00.706
- You know, that can happen.
- Could you just...

02:00.736 --> 02:02.441
Just hold on a second.
Let me tell you this.

02:02.471 --> 02:04.743
Maybe he thinks that my conclusions
are just, you know, inconclusive.

02:04.773 --> 02:06.040
Oh, God!

02:07.876 --> 02:10.311
This could be terrible
for my whole career.

02:10.378 --> 02:11.879
I just have to calm down.

02:12.381 --> 02:13.548
Calm down.

02:13.616 --> 02:15.416
I'm gonna go take a hot bath.

02:15.484 --> 02:17.152
Thanks for listening.

02:17.219 --> 02:20.955
I'm gonna go stick
my head in the microwave.

02:21.023 --> 02:23.458
With my mouth open
so it doesn't explode.

